>break began 5 years ago at Lotus--which madated that we use
>Microsoft C5. At the time MSC had a problem with fragmented
>memory and our original programmer couldn't fix it. I came in
>and spent many-many hours narrowing down the problem--the
>tech support at Microsoft couldn't help--I was basically on
